The paper deals with a classical signal processing problem of line spectral estimation, which involves estimating the spectral lines of a signal from its noisy measurements. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.SP), and statistical inference (cs.SI). The paper also proposes algorithms for solving the problem, which involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT and cs.SP, followed by cs.SI, cs.NA, and cs.LG.
